def: Pertaining to, derived from, or resembling, nonane; as, nonoicacid, which is also called pelargonic acid. Cf. Pelargonic.
The act of labefying or making weak; the state of beingweakened; decay; ruin.There is in it such a labefaction of all principles as may beinjurious to morality. Johnson.
Knowledge of the earth, ground, or soil, obtained byinspection. Chambers.

Of or pertaining to an alkali or to alkalies; having theproperties of an alkali. Alkaline earths, certain substances, aslime, baryta, strontia, and magnesia, possessing some of thequalities of alkalies.-- Alkaline metals, potassium, sodium, c√¶sium, lithium, rubidium.-- Alkaline reaction, a reaction indicating alkalinity, as by theaction on limits, turmeric, etc.
Not sanitary; unhealthy; as, insanitary conditions of drainage.
Cursing; imprecatory; vilifying. Carlyle.-- Ex"e*cra*tive*ly, adv.
Of or pertaining to theosophy; theosophical.
A king; a prince; a chief; a governor; -- so called among theTartars, Turks, and Persians, and in countries now or formerlygoverned by them.
Felt in one's own breast; inward; private. "Home-felt quiet.Pope.
